
Variation
---------

Small changes have driven extinction

Climate has been stable enough to allow adaptation to various climates
throughout the world.

Slight shift in average temp have large effects 


Chemistry
---------

Normal process: CO2 absorbed by plants which release Oxygen while alive and
Carbon when they die and decompose.


History
--------

Great Famine of 1315-17 - slight lowering of temps caused famine


